(5s + 10s + 20s between retries). All four tests need `#[tokio::test(start_paused = true)]` to avoid real wall-clock backoff delays in CI.","rationale":"Verified: `resume_from_failed_run_skips_completed_stages` took 35.03s and `resume_from_failed_docs_change_run_skips_completed_stages` took 35.02s. Even after fixing the transient failure count, these tests will each add ~60s+ of real time (5s+10s+20s+40s backoff for 5 attempts) without `start_paused`."}],"summary":"The implementation is solid across its four main changes: (1) retry limit increases are correctly applied in `retry_policy.rs`, (2) timeout enforcement via `tokio::time::timeout` in `process_backend.rs` correctly wraps I/O + process wait with proper SIGKILL cleanup, (3) the new `BinaryNotFound` failure class is properly integrated (enum variant, serde, as_str, terminal retry rule, classify_exit_failure for both spawn NotFound and exit 127), and (4) exponential backoff in the engine retry loop is correctly computed and capped. However, 4 existing \"resume from failed run\" tests are broken: they configure only 3 transient failures but TransportFailure now allows 5 attempts, so the run succeeds instead of failing. These same tests also lack `start_paused = true`, causing ~35s real-time backoff delays per test."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"83d94144-73c5-4143-907b-b916f164c2f1"}
